-- Sacos Trades for First Day as Seychelles Exchange Opens
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2013-08-08T15:57:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-08/sacos-trades-for-first-day-as-seychelles-exchange-opens.html
Sacos Group, a formerly state-owned
insurance and property investment business, became the first
company to start trading its shares on the Seychelles’ stock
exchange today.  The country’s biggest insurer on the Indian Ocean island
nation, closed trade at 68 Seychelles rupees on the Seychelles
Securities Exchange, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  “This is a very exciting moment for Seychelles, the launch
of the first day of trading for the Seychelles Securities
Exchange,” Pierre Laporte, the country’s finance minister said,
according to an e-mailed copy of a speech made at the opening
ceremony. “The development of  capital markets  for Seychelles
reflects the great steps that Seychelles has taken in our
economic reform agenda.”  SACOS Group owns SACOS Insurance Co. Ltd., SACOS Life
Assurance Co. and Sun Investment Ltd. The company’s asset value
as of Dec. 31 was 606 million rupees ($51 million), according to
documentation released at the opening ceremony.  The government of Seychelles owns 20 percent of the company
while Opportunities Investment has 37.1 percent, it said earlier
this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
